#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.115"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.115:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:0.2"
msgid "12. Dhammakathikavagga "
msgstr "12. A Dhamma speaker "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 115. Dhammakathikasutta → kathika 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.115:0.3"
msgid "115. Dhammakathikasutta "
msgstr "115. A Dhamma speaker "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.164, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.3"
msgid "“‘dhammakathiko, dhammakathiko’ti, bhante, vuccati; "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of a ‘Dhamma speaker’. "

msgctxt "sn22.115:1.4"
msgid "kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, dhammakathiko hotī”ti? "
msgstr "How is a Dhamma speaker defined?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.5"
msgid "“Rūpassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti ‘dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, if a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding form, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who speaks on Dhamma’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.6"
msgid "Rūpassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, ‘dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "If they practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding form, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in line with the teaching’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.7"
msgid "Rūpassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādāvimutto hoti, ‘diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding form, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who has attained extinguishment in this very life’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.8"
msgid "Vedanāya ce, bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment with feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.115:1.9"
msgid "saññāya ce, bhikkhu … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.115:1.10"
msgid "saṅkhārānañce, bhikkhu … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.115:1.11"
msgid "viññāṇassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "consciousness, for its fading away and cessation, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who speaks on Dhamma’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.12"
msgid "Viññāṇassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, ‘dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "If they practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding consciousness, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in line with the teaching’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.13"
msgid "Viññāṇassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādāvimutto hoti, ‘diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding consciousness, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who has attained extinguishment in this very life’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.115:1.14"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

